                            <comment id="12623874" author="jimk" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2008 01:57:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why? For convenience? All truncate does is &quot;disable &amp;lt;table name&amp;gt;&quot;, &quot;delete &amp;lt;table name&amp;gt;&quot;, and &quot;create &amp;lt;table name&amp;gt;&quot;; possibly only saving the specification of the schema (HTableDescriptor) required to recreate the table.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12623892" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2008 03:09:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this would be convenient since, during development, tables are dropped often only to be recreated. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12623894" author="jdcryans" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2008 03:59:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that truncates a table using some of the other irb commands.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
